Linear Regression

Used for predicting continuous values by fitting a straight line to the data.

Logistic Regression

Used for classification problems, especially binary classification (e.g., yes/no).

Decision Trees

A tree-like model that splits data based on conditions to make decisions.

K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)

Classifies data points based on the majority class of their nearest neighbors.

Support Vector Machines (SVM)

Finds the optimal boundary (hyperplane) that separates different classes.
